@startmindmap
!theme plain
skinparam dpi 150
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam NodeBackgroundColor #EBF8FF
skinparam NodeBorderColor #2B6CB0
skinparam ArrowColor #4A5568

<style>
mindmapDiagram {
  .problem {
    BackgroundColor #2B6CB0
    FontColor #FFFFFF
    FontStyle bold
    FontSize 13
  }
  .category {
    BackgroundColor #BEE3F8
    FontStyle bold
    FontSize 11
  }
  .sub {
    BackgroundColor #EBF8FF
    FontSize 10
  }
}
</style>

title BankFlow - Ishikawa Diagram (6 Ms)

* Demo-Ready\nBankFlow MVP\nAt Risk <<problem>>

** Manpower <<category>>
*** Limited internship-prototype bandwidth <<sub>>
*** Banking-domain learning curve <<sub>>
*** Split ownership across builder,\nbackend, and runtime changes <<sub>>
*** Security and audit implementation\nskills still maturing <<sub>>

** Methods <<category>>
*** Legacy HRFlow execution model\nis too n8n-centric <<sub>>
*** Flow publish/versioning strategy\nnot fully settled <<sub>>
*** Route hardening and auth coverage\nstill incomplete in places <<sub>>
*** Migration path from workflow runs\nto BankFlow case runtime is complex <<sub>>

** Machine <<category>>
*** In-process orchestrator still\nneeds to become the runtime core <<sub>>
*** Scheduler/polling approach may\nstrain SLA handling as scope grows <<sub>>
*** n8n callback and correlation handling\nadds integration fragility <<sub>>
*** Local Docker/dev stack adds\nsetup and debugging overhead <<sub>>

left side

** Materials <<category>>
*** HR-specific templates, labels,\nand sample flows still need cleanup <<sub>>
*** Unsupported builder nodes exist\nwithout full runtime support <<sub>>
*** Schema and migration debt from\nthe HRFlow fork remains <<sub>>
*** Committed runtime artifacts/backups\nneed sanitization and removal <<sub>>

** Measurement <<category>>
*** Regression coverage is still limited\nfor approvals, escalations, and SLA flows <<sub>>
*** Audit completeness is a requirement\nbut not yet automatically verified <<sub>>
*** Approval time, escalation rate,\nand overdue metrics are not yet baselined <<sub>>
*** Dashboard and oversight success\ncriteria need concrete acceptance checks <<sub>>

** Mother Nature <<category>>
*** Tight MVP timeline constrains\nscope and engineering depth <<sub>>
*** Banking governance raises the bar\nfor security and traceability <<sub>>
*** External integration variability\ncan disrupt demo reliability <<sub>>
*** Evolving requirements pressure the team\nto prioritize only two core use cases <<sub>>

@endmindmap
